%
% Bibliography file for the ICU sedation digital twin paper. This file
% stores all citations in BibTeX format, which LaTeX uses to automatically
% generate the references section of the paper. Each entry has a unique
% citation key that you use in the paper text with \cite{key}.
%
% The general structure of a BibTeX entry is to start with the entry type
% in @brackets followed by the citation key, then a list of fields like
% author, title, journal, year, and so on. Different entry types are
% used for different kinds of sources, with @article for journal papers,
% @inproceedings for conference papers, @book for books, and @misc for
% miscellaneous sources like websites.
%
% As you add citations to the paper, add the corresponding entries here.
% Most academic search engines including PubMed and Google Scholar can
% export citations in BibTeX format, so you usually do not have to type
% these by hand. Just be sure to verify that the exported entries are
% complete and accurate before using them.
%
% =====================================================================

